Q.
Create a database called Reminders.
Create a table inside that named TodoList with columns as id, item and time_taken. Use appropriate data types.
Insert values into that table.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Ans.
create database Remainders;
create table TodoList(id tinyint, item varchar(30), time_taken tinyint);
insert into TodoList values(1,"Learn HTML",45),(2,"Tea break",10),(3,"Learn CSS",45),(4,"Snack break",10),(5,"Learn JS",45),(6,"Lunch break",30),(7,"Learn database",45),(8,"Nap time",30);
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Output:
select * from TodoList;
+------+----------------+------------+
| id   | item           | time_taken |
+------+----------------+------------+
|    1 | Learn HTML     |         45 |
|    2 | Tea break      |         10 |
|    3 | Learn CSS      |         45 |
|    4 | Snack break    |         10 |
|    5 | Learn JS       |         45 |
|    6 | Lunch break    |         30 |
|    7 | Learn database |         45 |
|    8 | Nap time       |         30 |
+------+----------------+------------+
